"{\"abstract\":\"This paper demonstrates an opinion indicator (OI) generation system, named Crowd View, with which traders can refer to the fine-grained opinions, beyond the market sentiment (bullish/bearish), from crowd investors when trading financial instruments. We collect the real-time textual information from Twitter, and convert it into five kinds of OIs, including the support price level, resistance price level, price target, buy-side cost, and sell-side cost. The OIs for all component stocks in Dow Jones Industrial Average Index (DJI) are provided, and shown with the real-time stock price for comparison and analysis. The information embedding in the OIs and the application scenarios are introduced.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3376667\",\"name\":\"Chung-Chi Chen\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3376667\"},{\"authorId\":\"2611607\",\"name\":\"Hen-Hsen Huang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2611607\"},{\"authorId\":\"50847412\",\"name\":\"H. Chen\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/50847412\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"2005.01897\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3376667\",\"name\":\"Chung-Chi Chen\"},{\"authorId\":\"2611607\",\"name\":\"Hen-Hsen Huang\"},{\"authorId\":\"153924342\",\"name\":\"Hsin-Hsi Chen\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"methodology\",\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"3d9a08afe6c34db82d83d6927d2cbd8de4be44e0\",\"title\":\"Fine-grained Financial Opinion Mining: A Survey and Research Agenda\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/3d9a08afe6c34db82d83d6927d2cbd8de4be44e0\",\"venue\":\"ArXiv\",\"year\":2020},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3376667\",\"name\":\"Chung-Chi Chen\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"97a223895354de39bd6ac1ba2cddc14946e9bb8e\",\"title\":\"Overview of the NTCIR-15 FinNum-2 Task: Numeral Attachment in Financial Tweets\",\"url\":\"https://w